did.head: Descriptive Summary
did.unittitle: The Virginia Room Vertical and Historic Landmark Files, Undated
did.abstract: The Virginia Room Vertical and Historic Landmark Files consist of over 2,000 files on Fairfax County historical landmarks, communities, buildings, neighborhoods, churches, schools, and general county topics. The files contain newspaper clippings, reports, brochures, photocopies, correspondence, ephemera, and articles.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: Virginia Room Vertical and Historic Landmark Files, Virginia Room, Fairfax County Public Library

acqinfo.head: Acquisition Information
acqinfo.p: Collection created by Virginia Room staff over a period of years

processinfo.head: Processing Information
processinfo.p:

EAD generated by Ross Landis, 2017

bioghist.head: Historical and Biographical Information
bioghist.p: With the establishment of the Virginiana Collection of the Fairfax County Public Library in the mid-1950s, Virginia Room librarians have continuously maintained vertical subject files on Fairfax County’s history and infrastructure. The Virginia Room Vertical and Historic Landmark Files consist of over 2,000 files on Fairfax County historical landmarks, communities, buildings, neighborhoods, churches, schools, and general county topics. The files contain newspaper clippings, reports, brochures, photocopies, correspondence, ephemera, and articles.

Subject files are located in two different file cabinets in the Virginia Room. Files that have an “HLF” prefix are found in the Historic Landmark File cabinets while files with a “VF” are found in the Vertical Files cabinets.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Content
scopecontent.p: The Virginia Room Vertical and Historic Landmark Files consist of over 2,000 files containing newspaper clippings, reports, brochures, photocopies, correspondence, ephemera, and articles on Fairfax County’s history and infrastructure.
